----------------------------------------------------------------------------
ZMC, source distribution, README.1ST

(1) Introduction
(1a) Compiling
(2) Installation
(3) Running
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
(1) Introduction

This archive source files for compiling ZMC on gfortran.
It was developed on a Linux platform using Intel Fortran Compiler, 
then ported to g95 and then gfortran. 

Please refer to ZMC's built-in help, and to the incomplete manual 
ZMC_handbook_incomplete.pdf and to the papers that use the program.

All use should reference the paper:
 D. J. Goossens, A. P. Heerdegen, E. J. Chan & T. R. Welberry, 'Monte
 Carlo Modelling of Diffuse Scattering from Single Crystals: The 
 Program ZMC' Metallurgical and Materials Transactions A, vol 42A, 
 (2011) 23-31.  DOI:10.1007/s11661-010-0199-1

Program was modified in 2026 to get it to comile and run under the then-current
version of gfortran:

GNU Fortran (Debian 14.2.0-19) 14.2.0
